article.headline: Miami (Ohio) 52, Florida A&M 33
article.story: OXFORD, Ohio (AP) -- Tim Pollitz scored 16 points and had 11 rebounds to lead Miami of Ohio to a 52-33 win over cold-shooting Florida A&M Friday night. The Rattlers (1-2) shot 4-for-21 in the first half and 12-for-48 overall, including 0-for-17 on 3-pointers. The RedHawks (1-2) shot 37 percent -- 20 for 54 -- and started the game on a 14-2 run over the first seven minutes. Miami took a 26-11 lead at halftime and never led by fewer than 11 points in the second half. Michael Bramos scored 13 points for Miami. Lamar Twitty led Florida A&M with eight points.
